      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 263: The STUN controls are added inside connectivityView(), which is rendered for both SIP and non-SIP accounts in body. The change subject is SIP connectivity, and these settings use SIP account config keys; exposing them for Jami accounts can save unsupported/irrelevant STUN settings. Gate the STUN section the same way publicAddressView() is gated, or move it into the SIP-only branch.\n```suggestion\nif model.account.type \u003d\u003d .sip {\n    ToggleCell(\n        toggleText: L10n.AccountPage.stunEnabled,\n        getAction: { model.stunEnabled },\n        setAction: { newValue in model.enableStun(enable: newValue) }\n    )\n\n    if model.stunEnabled {\n        NavigationLink(destination: EditableFieldView(value: $model.stunServer, title: L10n.AccountPage.stunServer, placeholder: L10n.AccountPage.stunServer, onDisappearAction: {\n            model.saveStunSettings()\n        })) {\n            FieldRowView(label: L10n.AccountPage.stunServer, value: model.stunServer)\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
