      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 286: The published port is edited as an unrestricted text field and saved directly to account details. This allows non-numeric or out-of-range values to be persisted, which can break SIP registration/connectivity and leaves validation to lower layers. Use a numeric editor or validate before saving, e.g. reject empty/non-integer values and enforce 1...65535 before calling setPublishedAddressSettings.\n```suggestion\nNavigationLink(destination: EditableFieldView(value: $model.publishedPort,\n                                                  title: L10n.AccountPage.publishedPort,\n                                                  placeholder: L10n.AccountPage.publishedPort,\n                                                  onDisappearAction: {\n                                                    guard let port \u003d Int(model.publishedPort), (1...65535).contains(port) else { return }\n                                                    model.savePublishedAddressSettings()\n                                                  })) {\n    FieldRowView(label: L10n.AccountPage.publishedPort, value: model.publishedPort)\n}\n```",
